uclear bunker busters</span><hr size=1> I think the Bush administration wants to pursue such technology. In the present climate (war) I can see them getting the go ahead despite ecowackies trying to suppress them. War is always good for technological progress. The luddites don't get heard. It's a high price to pay for nuclear technology advancement but I foresee a very long war. Terrorism groups are like cockroaches. For every one you stamp out there are a million more hiding in dark places. The only way to win this new kind of war is with new kinds of technology. Traditional warfare won't suffice. <br>
Then there is the mounting cost. Without succeeding with wholly new methods the US faces bankruptcy if it wishes to pursue this war indefinately. Bunker Busting tactical nukes would be a fearful weapon. There would be nowhere for terrorists to hide. A subterranean bunker in the middle of a Desert could be vapourised in an instant and anyone hiding in such places would be living with the knowledge they could be dead at any moment. Most would probably die of ulcers before even being located. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=johnfraz>John Fraz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_yingyang.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 245<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/23/02 5:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lneilsmith.com/tools/littlelogo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   GBU-28</span><hr size=1> Not nuclear, but definitely a point of data here.<br>
