h=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomicconspiracy>Atomic Conspiracy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/6/02 5:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Kinetic energy weapon</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What about using a long metal spike 2-3 feet in diameter, 20 feet long, and made of mostly solid iron.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Such a thing would weigh between 10 and 20 tons, but it would certainly have the necessary penetration. The GBU-28 guided bomb weighs around 2 1/2 tons, impacts at around mach 1, and will penetrate up to 15 meters of solid rock. If we increase mass by a factor of 4 and impact velocity by a factor of 15 or 20, we have several times the penetration. By the time this slug stops, it will have been heated to incandescent temperature, high enough to turn iron into an explosive gas when it contacts air in the targeted tunnel. <br>
I believe it would offer a higher capability than the mini-nuke. The cost, though high, would not be excessive. For one thing, orbital velocity is desirable but not absolutely necessary and this brings it within the short range payload capability of existing missiles. <br>
Such a thing was proposed a few years ago as an alternate payload for the Trident missile; the Pentagon referred to it as a &quot;flechette&quot; or kinetic energy warhead. The Trident version was not as heavy as what you propose but it was similar in many respects. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tim1965>Tim1965</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/8/02 2:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  reply</span><hr size=1> A kkv bunker buster from space would require a heat<br>
