The Shuttle and various capsules are a poor comparison for another reason, one that is often overlooked. These vehicles must lose essentially all of their peak velocity before they reach the ground. This means converting it to thermal energy through aerodynamic drag. A kkv is optimized to lose as little of its velocity as possible. <br>
<br>
Our old friend, the square cube law, also comes into play here. Take two solid slug kkv's: One, A, weighs 10 kg. The other, B, weighs 10,000 kg. Given identical shape and density, B will be 10 times as large in each dimension, it will have 100 times the surface area (dimension squared) but 1000 times the mass (dimension cubed). <br>
Aerodynamic losses are proportional to surface area. Given the same initial velocity, total kinetic energy is proportional to mass. Larger objects have much less surface area per unit mass, and will undergo much less heating per unit mass during the conversion, 1/10 as much for &quot;B&quot; vs. &quot;A&quot; in fact.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomicconspiracy>Atomic Conspiracy</A> at: 11/8/02 7:23:35 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=202.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=202.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=17><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=202.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.threadControl?topicID=202.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=202.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=202.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/u